The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, February 23, 2004 				 BJP leader sues Sonia
																								Hajipur, Feb. 22 (PTI): A case has been filed against Congress president Sonia Gandhi in a district court here for allegedly defaming the central government and the country by saying Vajpayees government is misleading the people through advertisements about its achievements.																								A BJP district leader, Bal Krishna Singh, filed the case in the court of Vaishali chief judicial magistrate yesterday.																								Singh filed the case on the basis of a news item in a daily datelined Bhadoi, Uttar Pradesh. It quoted the Congress chief as saying the central government was running a misleading advertisement campaign in newspapers and on television to highlight its achievements. 
